Package com.abstratt.simon.metamodel

Interface Metamodel

All Known Subinterfaces:
EcoreMetamodel
public interface Metamodel
Describes a metamodel. A metamodel is a set of types. Types may be:
  • values or objects: objects have identity, can have relationships. Values have no identity: primitive values, enumerated values, records
  • atomic or structured: an atomic type has no parts, a structured type (objects, records) is made of parts
See Also:
Metamodel.Slotted, Metamodel.Feature

    static interface  Metamodel.Named
    Model elements that may be named, should implement Named.
    static interface  Metamodel.ObjectType
    An object is a model element that can contain others, and contain reference to others.
    static interface  Metamodel.Primitive
    Primitive types are basic types that are not slotted (like Metamodel.RecordType) or Metamodel.Enumerated.
    static class  Metamodel.PrimitiveKind
    Metamodels may support many primitive types, but they must be of one of the kinds described here.
    static interface  Metamodel.RecordType
    A record is a model element that can contain basic values.
    static interface  Metamodel.Reference
    A feature that depicts a reference to another (non-owned) object.
    static interface  Metamodel.Slot
    A slot is a feature that can hold a basic value.
    static interface  Metamodel.Slotted
    A type for values that are made up of slots, such as Metamodel.RecordType and Metamodel.ObjectType.
    static interface  Metamodel.Type
    The basic interface for all types.
    static interface  Metamodel.Typed<T extends Metamodel.Type>
    An interface for data elements that can have a type.
